Follow `AGENTS.md` at the workspace root (repo map, hard invariants, TDD rules, grounding loop, commands) and the nearest nested `AGENTS.md` inside each repo (`repos/anki/AGENTS.md`, `repos/Anki-Android-Backend/AGENTS.md`).

Non-negotiables:
- Mutating backend ops go through `Collection::transact(Op::X, …)` returning `OpChanges`; never write the DB directly.
- `proto/anki/*.proto`: append-only new field numbers; never renumber/reuse.
- TDD: failing test first; tests are read-only to the implementer; never weaken a test to pass; `eval/holdout/` is off-limits.
- Ground every API via Serena (LSP)/ast-grep/`cargo check` before editing. Show file paths + line numbers first.
- AGPL-3.0-or-later on every new file; credit Anki.
